title: Homes Fit for Heroes: 100 Years of Council Housing
description:
What lasting effects have the rise and fall of council housing had on our politics, society and economy? Is it time to reconsider public housing?

A lecture by Professor Steve Schifferes, City University of London
3 February 2020 6:00pm UK Time
https://www.gresham.ac.uk/lectures-and-events/council-housing

More council houses were built in Britain than any other country in the 20th century. By the 1970s one in three households were council tenants. Yet after 1980 £100bn worth of council housing was sold off. How did this expansion come about, what changed – and what lasting effects did the rise and fall of council housing have on our politics, society and economy? Is it now time to reconsider our attitude to public housing?
